 For an FNS authorized retailer with Program benefit redemption
amounting to 15 percent or more of total food sales, all checkout
lanes shall be equipped;

 Describe all terms and conditions with respect to equipment
ownership, lease arrangements, handling and maintenance for which
the State agency and merchant are liable;

 Third party processors shall be liable for transactions until the
transaction has been electronically accepted by the contracted
vendor or an intermediate processing facility;

 Follow-up on actions taken regarding any disqualification or
withdrawal of an authorized retailer from the Program must occur
within two business days after receipt;

 Ensure that equipment and supplies are maintained in working order
for retail stores equipped by the State agency or its contractor.
Equipment shall be replaced or repaired within 48 hours;

 Reconciliation of benefits posted to household accounts on the
central computer against benefits on the Issuance Authorization
File;

 Reconciliation of each individual retail store's SNAP
transactions per POS terminal and in total to deposits on a daily
basis;

 Determining the sufficiency of the household's account balance
in order to debit or credit household benefit accounts at the point
of sale;

 Preparing a daily tape in a National Automated Clearinghouse format
or other process approved by FNS with information on benefits
redeemed for each retailer and in summary;

 Range checks for acceptable date fields, number and valid account
numbers, purchase and refund upper limitations in order to prevent
and control damage to the system accounts;

 Passwords, identity codes or other security procedures must be
utilized by State agency or local personnel and at data processing
centers;

 Preparing a daily ACH tape or other crediting process approved by
FNS with information on benefits redeemed and creditable to each
retailer;

 The manual transaction occurred because the host computer was down
and authorization was obtained by the retailer for the transaction;
or

 The EBT processor may provide partial approval of the
store-and-forward transaction, crediting the retailer with the
balance remaining in the account through a one-step process;
